title: Here Are the 5K+ Items the Jets Are Bringing to London
text: Here Are the 5K+ Items the Jets Are Bringing to London For a 65-hour trip By Evann Gastaldo   Oct 1, 2015 6:39 PM CDT COMMENTS (0) (Newser) – The New York Jets are playing the Miami Dolphins at London's Wembley Stadium Sunday—and though the Jets will only be overseas for 65 hours, the team is bringing a lot of stuff. The New York Times takes an amusing look: 220 people in the delegation 350 rolls of toilet paper (because the kind used in England is too thin) 263 boxes or cases of food 315 power devices, from extension cords to adapters 472 pieces of athletic training supplies, from ice bags to tape 2,683 pieces of equipment, from T-shirts to knee pads 1,268 promo items, from mini helmets to key chains Click for the entire amusing look at the 11-month planning process. New York Jets quarterback Ryan Fitzpatrick (14) walks off the field during the fourth quarter of an NFL football game against the Philadelphia Eagles, Sunday, Sept. 27, 2015, in East Rutherford, N.J.
